From: Stephen Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

The following background information on poliomyelitis in India was
extracted from GIDEON http://www.cyinfo.com: As of 1996, the median patient
age is below 2 years, and over 90% are under the age of 5 years.
Vaccination:
- Routine immunization (OPV) is administered at ages 1.5, 2.5, 3.5, and 16
to 24 months.
- Vaccine coverage was 94% in 1994; 91% as of 1997 (serosurveys estimate
the real figure at 73%); 73% in 1998.
- 90 million children were immunized in 1995. 125 million were immunized
during a one-day campaign in 1996, and an additional 120 million in 1997.
