[As I could not understand what "due to wild (type) virus" means in the
table above, I asked Steve Berger for clarifying information, if he had it.
Here is his response: "I too am confused. These terms are used by WHO,
and the remainder are not further defined. We can assume that the
remainder are due to 1) cases not sent for laboratory testing, 2) cases due
to vaccine virus (only a small number), or 3) Acute Flaccid Paralysis
[AFP. The most common causes of AFP are Guillaine Barre syndrome followed
by transverse myelitis. To complicate things even further, tables coming
from WHO during the past few years continue to list cases of polio (wild
virus in parentheses) as well as (cases of) AFP. There is no way to tell
if the AFP cases are included in (the totals for) polio, or as a separate
entity." - Mod.CHC .........................chc/es
